# HYCS .env.example
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HYCS is a public, contributor-friendly project. It runs FULLY CLIENT-SIDE
# by default — no built-in backend is required to use it. Copy this file to
# `.env` only if you need server-side image search; everything else is
# configured per-user inside the in-app Settings page.
#
# NEVER commit your real .env file. It is gitignored.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ===========================================================================
# AUTH / DATABASE — Bring Your Own Supabase
# ===========================================================================
# HYCS no longer ships with a built-in account system. End-users (and you,
# when developing) plug their own Supabase project into Settings → Your
# Supabase. The project URL and anon key are stored ONLY in the user's
# browser (localStorage). Nothing here in .env is required for auth.
#
# If you want a personal dev Supabase to test BYO-Supabase flows, paste
# the credentials into the in-app Settings panel — not here.

# ===========================================================================
# AI PROVIDERS — Bring Your Own Key
# ===========================================================================
# HYCS does not ship with a default AI gateway. Every contributor/user adds
# their own provider key in Settings → AI Providers (BYOK). Groq, OpenAI,
# Gemini, and Claude are supported. Keys are stored client-side only.

# ===========================================================================
# IMAGE SEARCH (optional, server-side)
# ===========================================================================
# Used by src/lib/fetch-image.functions.ts to source hero / project images.
# Without these the app falls back to Unsplash source URLs.
PEXELS_API_KEY=""
PIXABAY_API_KEY=""

# ===========================================================================
# DEPLOY HELPERS
# ===========================================================================
# GitHub Personal Access Tokens for the in-app deploy feature are stored
# client-side via Settings → Connections → GitHub. Do not put them here.
